call mcp with tool \"aar_wait_for_opportunity\" and empty args.\n\nLet me confirm that the arguments for mcp are structured correctly. The mcp function's arguments must have tool and args, each being strings. Because args is supposed to be a JSON string. So in the mcp call's arguments, \"args\" key is a string containing the JSON.\n\nYes. So for example, if the args for the tool is an empty object, then args parameter is the string \"{}\".\n\nSo the tool call for mcp is {\"name\": \"mcp\", \"arguments\": {\"tool\": \"aar_wait_for_opportunity\", \"args\": \"{}\"}}\n\nYes. Let's make that call first.","contentIndex":0,"partial":{"api":"openai-completions","content":[{"thinking":"","thinkingSignature":"reasoning","type":"thinking"},{"arguments":{"args":"{}","tool":"aar_wait_for_opportunity"},"id":"call_022d061fabea43788cf198","name":"mcp","type":"toolCall"}],"model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1782830079-xuxQdZ1LajiOrKj9aPGp","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509","role":"assistant","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782830079587,"usage":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"input":0,"output":0,"total":0},"input":2406,"output":1043,"totalTokens":3449}},"type":"thinking_end"},"message":{"api":"openai-completions","content":[{"thinking":"","thinkingSignature":"reasoning","type":"thinking"},{"arguments":{"args":"{}","tool":"aar_wait_for_opportunity"},"id":"call_022d061fabea43788cf198","name":"mcp","type":"toolCall"}],"model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1782830079-xuxQdZ1LajiOrKj9aPGp","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509","role":"assistant","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782830079587,"usage":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"input":0,"output":0,"total":0},"input":2406,"output":1043,"totalTokens":3449}},"type":"message_update"}
