ports in the western part of Iran's flight information region, known as the Tehran FIR, had been suspended until Monday, with only a limited number of airports allowed to operate\"\n\nKey considerations:\n- The rule doesn't require a countrywide closure, just a major Iranian airspace region.\n- The Tehran FIR (Flight Information Region) is a major Iranian airspace region.\n- The NOTAM clearly states \"ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART OF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD\" (with some exceptions).\n- The exceptions are described as \"operational from sunrise to sunset with fresh CAA permission\" for civil IFR passenger flights.\n- According to the rule, \"limited exceptions to a broad closure, however, will not disqualify such a closure from counting.\"\n\nThe raw NOTAM text shows:\n- A broad suspension (\"all airports in west part of Tehran FIR are closed\")\n- With exceptions for specific airports that can operate only under restricted conditions (daylight hours with new permission)\n\nThis meets the definition of a \"major closure\" with limited exceptions that don't disqualify it per the rule.\n\nThe Iran International report (DX-2) does deny a \"new nationwide\" notice and claims flights are \"normal\", but it simultaneously acknowledges the \"western part of Tehran FIR\" airport activity was suspended \"with only a limited number of airports allowed to operate\".\n\nThe evidence does not prove complete suspension at two listed airports (e.g., IKA, THR, etc.), but it does prove a major regional closure of the western Tehran FIR with limited exceptions.\n\nConclusion:\nThe raw NOTAM text provides clear evidence of a broad closure in a major Iranian airspace region (western Tehran FIR) with limited exceptions to the closure in certain airports. The rule explicitly states limited exceptions don't defeat a broad closure.\n\nSo I should vote \"demonstrated\" because the evidence shows Iran initiated a major non-weather closure of a major Iranian airspace region with limited exceptions that don't disqualify it.\n\nMy rationale: \"The raw NOTAM text confirms a broad closure of western Tehran FIR airports with specific exceptions that operate under limited daylight hours and fresh approval requirements, which meets the rule's definition of a major closure with permissible limited exceptions.\"","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ea3bac8bacea443aaf81f5","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The raw NOTAM text confirms a broad closure of western Tehran FIR with specific exceptions operating under limited daylight hours and fresh approval requirements, which meets the rule's definition of a major closure with permissible limited exceptions.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The raw NOTAM text confirms a broad closure of western Tehran FIR with specific exceptions operating under limited daylight hours and fresh approval requirements, which meets the rule's definition of a major closure with permissible limited exceptions.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782830086931,"responseId":"gen-1782830087-5naWeFrqnDM1B7yuCc3l","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to review the case details and the submitted evidence to make a decision. Let's identify the key evidence and the rule.\n\nThe case is about whether Iran initiated a major non-weather closure of its airspace by May 24, 2026 by 11:59 PM ET.\n\nThe rule (PX-1/DX-Rule) states that a \"major closure\" means:\n- A broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian airspace region, or\n- A non-weather complete suspension of commercial arrivals and departures affecting at least two listed airports (IKA, THR, MHD, SYZ, IFN), and\n- With the understanding that limited exceptions to a broad closure (like per-flight approvals) don't disqualify it.\n\nThe relevant evidence:\n1. Plaintiff's evidence (PX-2, PX-3): Reports from Indian Express and Siasat stating that Iran issued NOTAM OIIX A1010/26 on May 22, closing the western part of Tehran FIR to civil flights, with only 8 airports operational during daylight hours with fresh CAA approval required for passenger flights.\n\n2. Defendant's evidence (DX-1): Raw NOTAM text from Notamify showing:\n   - A1010/26: \"ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART OF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD EXCEPT OITR, OIKK, OIAA, OISS, OIYY, OICC, OIGG, AND OIAW THAT ARE OPERATIONAL FM SUNRISE TO SUNSET...\"\n   - A1015/26 (replacement): \"ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART OF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD EXCEPT: OITR, OIKK, OIAA, OISS, OIYY, OICC, OIGG, OIAW, OIFM, OITL, OISR AND OIAM...\" (more airports added)\n\n3. Defendant's evidence (DX-2): IRAN International report stating:\n   - Iran's Civil Aviation Organization denied issuing \"a new official aviation notice imposing restrictions on the country's airspace and that flight conditions remained normal\"\n   - BUT also acknowledged \"activity at airports in the western part of Iran's flight information region, known as the Tehran FIR, had been suspended until Monday, with only a limited number of airports allowed to operate\"\n\nKey considerations:\n- The rule doesn't require a countrywide closure, just a major Iranian airspace region.\n- The Tehran FIR (Flight Information Region) is a major Iranian airspace region.\n- The NOTAM clearly states \"ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART OF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD\" (with some exceptions).\n- The exceptions are described as \"operational from sunrise to sunset with fresh CAA permission\" for civil IFR passenger flights.\n- According to the rule, \"limited exceptions to a broad closure, however, will not disqualify such a closure from counting.\"\n\nThe raw NOTAM text shows:\n- A broad suspension (\"all airports in west part of Tehran FIR are closed\")\n- With exceptions for specific airports that can operate only under restricted conditions (daylight hours with new permission)\n\nThis meets the definition of a \"major closure\" with limited exceptions that don't disqualify it per the rule.\n\nThe Iran International report (DX-2) does deny a \"new nationwide\" notice and claims flights are \"normal\", but it simultaneously acknowledges the \"western part of Tehran FIR\" airport activity was suspended \"with only a limited number of airports allowed to operate\".\n\nThe evidence does not prove complete suspension at two listed airports (e.g., IKA, THR, etc.), but it does prove a major regional closure of the western Tehran FIR with limited exceptions.\n\nConclusion:\nThe raw NOTAM text provides clear evidence of a broad closure in a major Iranian airspace region (western Tehran FIR) with limited exceptions to the closure in certain airports. The rule explicitly states limited exceptions don't defeat a broad closure.\n\nSo I should vote \"demonstrated\" because the evidence shows Iran initiated a major non-weather closure of a major Iranian airspace region with limited exceptions that don't disqualify it.\n\nMy rationale: \"The raw NOTAM text confirms a broad closure of western Tehran FIR airports with specific exceptions that operate under limited daylight hours and fresh approval requirements, which meets the rule's definition of a major closure with permissible limited exceptions.\"","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ea3bac8bacea443aaf81f5","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The raw NOTAM text confirms a broad closure of western Tehran FIR with specific exceptions operating under limited daylight hours and fresh approval requirements, which meets the rule's definition of a major closure with permissible limited exceptions.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The raw NOTAM text confirms a broad closure of western Tehran FIR with specific exceptions operating under limited daylight hours and fresh approval requirements, which meets the rule's definition of a major closure with permissible limited exceptions.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782830086931,"responseId":"gen-1782830087-5naWeFrqnDM1B7yuCc3l","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509"}}
{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_delta","contentIndex":1,"delta":"","partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to review the case details and the submitted evidence to make a decision. Let's identify the key evidence and the rule.\n\nThe case is about whether Iran initiated a major non-weather closure of its airspace by May 24, 2026 by 11:59 PM ET.\n\nThe rule (PX-1/DX-Rule) states that a \"major closure\" means:\n- A broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian airspace region, or\n- A non-weather complete suspension of commercial arrivals and departures affecting at least two listed airports (IKA, THR, MHD, SYZ, IFN), and\n- With the understanding that limited exceptions to a broad closure (like per-flight approvals) don't disqualify it.\n\nThe relevant evidence:\n1. Plaintiff's evidence (PX-2, PX-3): Reports from Indian Express and Siasat stating that Iran issued NOTAM OIIX A1010/26 on May 22, closing the western part of Tehran FIR to civil flights, with only 8 airports operational during daylight hours with fresh CAA approval required for passenger flights.\n\n2. Defendant's evidence (DX-1): Raw NOTAM text from Notamify showing:\n   - A1010/26: \"ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART OF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD EXCEPT OITR, OIKK, OIAA, OISS, OIYY, OICC, OIGG, AND OIAW THAT ARE OPERATIONAL FM SUNRISE TO SUNSET...\"\n   - A1015/26 (replacement): \"ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART OF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD EXCEPT: OITR, OIKK, OIAA, OISS, OIYY, OICC, OIGG, OIAW, OIFM, OITL, OISR AND OIAM...\" (more airports added)\n\n3. Defendant's evidence (DX-2): IRAN International report stating:\n   - Iran's Civil Aviation Organization denied issuing \"a new official aviation notice imposing restrictions on the country's airspace and that flight conditions remained normal\"\n   - BUT also acknowledged \"activity at airports in the western part of Iran's flight information region, known as the Tehran FIR, had been suspended until Monday, with only a limited number of airports allowed to operate\"\n\nKey considerations:\n- The rule doesn't require a countrywide closure, just a major Iranian airspace region.\n- The Tehran FIR (Flight Information Region) is a major Iranian airspace region.\n- The NOTAM clearly states \"ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART OF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD\" (with some exceptions).\n- The exceptions are described as \"operational from sunrise to sunset with fresh CAA permission\" for civil IFR passenger flights.\n- According to the rule, \"limited exceptions to a broad closure, however, will not disqualify such a closure from counting.\"\n\nThe raw NOTAM text shows:\n- A broad suspension (\"all airports in west part of Tehran FIR are closed\")\n- With exceptions for specific airports that can operate only under restricted conditions (daylight hours with new permission)\n\nThis meets the definition of a \"major closure\" with limited exceptions that don't disqualify it per the rule.\n\nThe Iran International report (DX-2) does deny a \"new nationwide\" notice and claims flights are \"normal\", but it simultaneously acknowledges the \"western part of Tehran FIR\" airport activity was suspended \"with only a limited number of airports allowed to operate\".\n\nThe evidence does not prove complete suspension at two listed airports (e.g., IKA, THR, etc.), but it does prove a major regional closure of the western Tehran FIR with limited exceptions.\n\nConclusion:\nThe raw NOTAM text provides clear evidence of a broad closure in a major Iranian airspace region (western Tehran FIR) with limited exceptions to the closure in certain airports. The rule explicitly states limited exceptions don't defeat a broad closure.\n\nSo I should vote \"demonstrated\" because the evidence shows Iran initiated a major non-weather closure of a major Iranian airspace region with limited exceptions that don't disqualify it.\n\nMy rationale: \"The raw NOTAM text confirms a broad closure of western Tehran FIR airports with specific exceptions that operate under limited daylight hours and fresh approval requirements, which meets the rule's definition of a major closure with permissible limited exceptions.\"","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ea3bac8bacea443aaf81f5","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The raw NOTAM text confirms a broad closure of western Tehran FIR with specific exceptions operating under limited daylight hours and fresh approval requirements, which meets the rule's definition of a major closure with permissible limited exceptions.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The raw NOTAM text confirms a broad closure of western Tehran FIR with specific exceptions operating under limited daylight hours and fresh approval requirements, which meets the rule's definition of a major closure with permissible limited exceptions.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782830086931,"responseId":"gen-1782830087-5naWeFrqnDM1B7yuCc3l","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to review the case details and the submitted evidence to make a decision. Let's identify the key evidence and the rule.\n\nThe case is about whether Iran initiated a major non-weather closure of its airspace by May 24, 2026 by 11:59 PM ET.\n\nThe rule (PX-1/DX-Rule) states that a \"major closure\" means:\n- A broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights tr